@version: [2, current]
@description: Remove a hook.
@lot:
- void
- string $id
- array $id
- string $id, string $name
- array $id, string $name
@static: 1
@example: |
  // Remove an attached `content` hook with ID `fn_meta` before execution,
  // or prevent a hook with ID `fn_meta` to be attached to the `content` container
  Hook::reset('content', 'fn_meta');

  // Remove all hook(s) attached to the `content` container
  Hook::reset('content');
@example-note: You cannot remove hooks that are attached using anonymous function because they have no ID.
